  "faqRegisterQuestion": "How to register an account?",
  "faqRegisterAnswer": "Download Gia Tộc Việt, tap \"Register\" and fill in your full name, email, and password. After successful registration, use the invite code from your Clan Leader to request to join your Clan.",
  "faqForgotPasswordQuestion": "I forgot my password, what should I do?",
  "faqForgotPasswordAnswer": "On the login screen, tap \"Forgot password\". Enter your registered email, the system will send a 6-digit OTP code via email. Enter the OTP to verify and set a new password.",
  "faqChangePasswordQuestion": "How to change password?",
  "faqChangePasswordAnswer": "Go to Settings > Account Security, enter your current password, then enter and confirm your new password. The password must have at least 8 characters.",
  "faqAddMemberQuestion": "How to add a new member?",
  "faqAddMemberAnswer": "Go to Dashboard, tap the \"+\" button on the Members tab. Fill in the information: full name, gender, date of birth, place of birth, generation, branch, parents (if any). You can add optional details like date of death, marital status, notes. Tap \"Save\" to finish. Requires Editor role or higher.",
  "faqAddBranchQuestion": "How to add a new branch?",
  "faqAddBranchAnswer": "Go to Dashboard, select the Branches tab and tap the \"+\" button. Enter the branch name, description, and founder information (if any). After creating, the Clan Leader can assign a Branch Admin to manage that branch.",
  "faqEditMemberQuestion": "How to edit member information?",
  "faqEditMemberAnswer": "In the member list, select the member to edit and tap the edit icon (pen). Update the information then tap \"Save\". Only Editors and higher roles can edit.",
  "faqDeleteMemberQuestion": "How to delete a member?",
  "faqDeleteMemberAnswer": "Select the member from the list, tap the delete icon (trash) and confirm. Note: only Clan Leaders and Branch Admins can delete members; Editors cannot delete.",
  "faqImportGenealogyQuestion": "Can I import genealogy from a file?",
  "faqImportGenealogyAnswer": "The app currently supports adding members manually. Bulk import from file is under development.",
  "faqInviteCodeQuestion": "How does the clan invite code work?",
  "faqInviteCodeAnswer": "Each Clan has a unique Invite Code generated by the system. The Clan Leader can view, copy, and share the Invite Code (along with a QR code) in the Dashboard. New members use this code to send a join request — approved by the Clan Leader or Branch Admin.",
  "faqRolesQuestion": "What are the roles in the Clan?",
  "faqRolesAnswer": "The system has 4 role levels:\n• Clan Leader — Highest authority: manages the entire Clan, assigns roles, transfers leadership, and dissolves.\n• Branch Admin — Manages assigned family branch, approves join requests.\n• Editor — Adds and edits member information (cannot delete).\n• Member — Views genealogy information and family events.",
  "faqAssignRoleQuestion": "How to assign roles to members?",
  "faqAssignRoleAnswer": "Go to Settings > Member Roles (only visible to Clan Leader). Select the member and choose the appropriate role. The Clan Leader cannot self-demote — use the Transfer Clan Leadership feature.",
  "faqTransferOwnershipQuestion": "How to transfer Clan Leadership?",
  "faqTransferOwnershipAnswer": "Go to Settings > Transfer Clan Leadership. Select a member with an activated account from the list. Confirm the transfer — this action cannot be undone. After transferring, you become a Member and the recipient becomes the new Clan Leader.",
  "faqDissolveClanQuestion": "How to dissolve a clan?",
  "faqDissolveClanAnswer": "Go to Settings > Dissolve Clan (Clan Leader only). Type the exact Clan name to confirm. All data — members, branches, genealogy — will be permanently deleted and cannot be recovered. This action cannot be undone.",
  "faqDataSecurityQuestion": "Is my genealogy data secure?",
  "faqDataSecurityAnswer": "Yes. All data is stored on servers in Vietnam, encrypted during transmission and storage. We comply with Decree 13/2023/NĐ-CP on personal data protection and commit not to share data with third parties. Clan information is only visible to approved members.",
  "faqDeleteAccountQuestion": "How to delete my account?",
  "faqDeleteAccountAnswer": "Go to Settings > Account Security, select \"Delete Account\" and confirm. Note: if you are Clan Leader, please transfer Clan Leadership or dissolve the Clan before deleting your account.",
  "faqMultiDeviceQuestion": "Can I use the app on multiple devices?",
  "faqMultiDeviceAnswer": "Yes. Your account can log in on multiple devices simultaneously, data will be synced in real-time. For security reasons, please log out from unused devices.",
  "faqEnglishSupportQuestion": "Does the app support English?",
  "faqEnglishSupportAnswer": "Yes. Go to Settings > Language, toggle the switch to change to English. The interface will update immediately. Genealogy data and member information remain intact.",
